# Testing Rules

## Rust
- Every function in instrument-core must have at least one unit test
- Test files sit alongside the code they test
- Use descriptive names: fn encodes_standard_ascii_string()
- Never use unwrap() in tests — use expect() with a message

## TypeScript / React
- Mock src/bridge/index.ts with vi.mock() — never need a running Tauri instance
- Mock callTool to return a Promise using vi.useFakeTimers()
  Never resolve synchronously — always simulate processing time
  Use vi.advanceTimersByTime() to step through async state transitions
  This ensures isLoading intermediate states are tested correctly
- Use userEvent from @testing-library/user-event for all interactions
- Test what the user sees — never test implementation details
